10
00:00:28,740 --> 00:00:31,350
in dependency injection.

11
00:00:31,350 --> 00:00:34,770
I want to spend some time to explain you few things

12
00:00:34,770 --> 00:00:36,540
right here.

13
00:00:36,540 --> 00:00:39,600
Now think about when you are implementing a login

14
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,120
or registration functionality.

15
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:44,670
You will have to write all the code

16
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:46,140
of what should happen

17
00:00:46,140 --> 00:00:49,440
when a user enters username and password.

18
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:51,780
You will have to encrypt that code.

19
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:53,640
You might have to validate that

20
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:55,980
with what it is there in database

21
00:00:55,980 --> 00:00:57,960
and then you can be like, okay,

22
00:00:57,960 --> 00:01:02,250
authentication looks good, login is successful.

23
00:01:02,250 --> 00:01:05,310
On top of that, you will have to store that in session

24
00:01:05,310 --> 00:01:08,190
or some place that user is logged in

25
00:01:08,190 --> 00:01:11,310
and you might have to store the details about user

26
00:01:11,310 --> 00:01:12,333
in session.

27
00:01:13,230 --> 00:01:16,110
Now these are only the basic things.

28
00:01:16,110 --> 00:01:18,750
If you think about the complete authentication

29
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:22,170
there are way more functionalities that are needed.

30
00:01:22,170 --> 00:01:24,450
Taking care of logging a user,

31
00:01:24,450 --> 00:01:26,820
all the way to logging out a user

32
00:01:26,820 --> 00:01:30,360
and managing their credentials between there.

33
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:32,848
When we use the .NET identity,

34
00:01:32,848 --> 00:01:37,830
.NET team has taken care of all the heavy lifting for us

35
00:01:37,830 --> 00:01:41,430
and they have given us these classes like SignInManager,

36
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:45,870
UserManager, RoleManager to manage your roles

37
00:01:45,870 --> 00:01:49,830
