55
00:02:36,450 --> 00:02:39,630
If you press F12 or if you scroll down,

56
00:02:39,630 --> 00:02:42,333
you will see that method right here.

57
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:45,600
That CreateUser is doing nothing

58
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:49,980
but it is creating an instance of IdentityUser.

59
00:02:49,980 --> 00:02:50,910
Rather than that

60
00:02:50,910 --> 00:02:54,930
we want to create an instance of ApplicationUser

61
00:02:54,930 --> 00:02:58,533
and we will have to update the return type here as well.

62
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:03,240
That will make sure that CreateUser right here,

63
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:06,873
the user will now be of type ApplicationUser.

64
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,300
Then on line 120,

65
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:13,020
you can see we have a helper method in _userManager,

66
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:15,000
which is CreateAsync,

67
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,270
there it expects a user object and password

68
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:22,110
and it will automatically create that user.

69
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:24,690
So when this method will be invoked

70
00:03:24,690 --> 00:03:28,890
it'll insert an entry in the ASP.NET user's table

71
00:03:28,890 --> 00:03:32,463
and on top of that it'll encrypt the password as well.

72
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:37,623
So helper method is taking care of all the heavy lifting.

73
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:42,480
On top of that, if result is successful, we scroll down.

74
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:45,660
It is also doing something to generate email token

75
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:47,460
and sending email,

76
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:49,800
but it is only the interface,

77
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,773
implementation of that has not been done.

78
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:57,060
But if you examine on line 144,

79
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:59,190
we are using _signInManager,

80
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:03,390
and we are automatically signing in that user.

81
00:04:03,390 --> 00:04:05,640
And because of that, if you remember,

82
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:09,330
when we register a user and hit the submit button

83
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:12,393
it automatically signs in the user.

84
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:15,150
We do not have to write any code,

85
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:17,399
we are only calling the helper method

86
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:20,583
in _signInManager and _userManager.

87
00:04:21,810 --> 00:04:23,460
So, that is great.

